Sentiment analysis

# read in files
pos_words <- scan('positive-words.txt', blank.lines.skip = TRUE, comment.char = ";", what = "")
neg_words <- scan('negative-words.txt', blank.lines.skip = TRUE, comment.char = ";", what = "")

glove <- read_delim('glove.42B.300d.txt', ' ', col_names=F, quote='')
colnames(glove) <- c('word', 1:300)

Set up training data

# train words
train_words <- tibble(word=c(pos_words, neg_words),
                      pos=rep(1:0, c(length(pos_words),length(neg_words))))

train.tbl <- inner_join(train_words, glove, by='word')

# create design matrix for 'glmnet'
train_x <- train.tbl %>% 
  select(-word, -pos) %>% 
  as.matrix()

rownames(train_x) <- train.tbl$word

# response
train_y <- train.tbl$pos

Model

# set test data
test <- sample(nrow(train_x), nrow(train_x)/5) # 20% as test data
# logistical model with a mix (50/50) mix of L1 and L2 regularisation.
fit <- cv.glmnet(train_x[-test,], train_y[-test], family = 'binomial', alpha = 0.5)
# prediction
pred <- predict(fit$glmnet.fit, train_x[test,], s = fit$lambda.min)
# random 20 prediction
pred[sample(nrow(pred),20),]

# function to process got lines
process_line <- function(string) {
  sent <- gsub('-', ' ',
          gsub('--', ' ',
          gsub('…', ' ',
          gsub('“', '',
          gsub('\\*', '', 
          gsub('”', '',
          gsub('\\[', '',
          gsub('\\]', '',
          gsub('‘', '', 
          gsub('\\\\', '',
          gsub('/', '', string) ))))))))))
  
  tolower(strsplit(sent,"[[:blank:],.!?;:'\"]")[[1]])
}

# split all lines into words
words <- sapply(got$Sentence, process_line)

# get unique words in all lines
unique_words <- unique(unlist(words))
got_glove <- glove %>% filter(word %in% unique_words)

# matrix for unique words with glove dimensions
m <- got_glove %>% select(-word) %>% as.matrix()

# get scores for unique words
scores <- predict(fit$glmnet.fit, m, s=fit$lambda.min)
got_word_scores <- got_glove %>% 
  select(word) %>%
  mutate(score=as.numeric(scores))

# function to get average score for each line in got script
get_score <- function(line){
  words <- process_line(line)
  word_tbl <- tibble(word=words)
  join <- inner_join(word_tbl, got_word_scores, by='word')
  if(nrow(join) == 0 ) return(0)
  mean(join$score)
}

# scores for each line
line_scores <- sapply(1:nrow(got), function(i) get_score(got$Sentence[i]))
got <- got %>% mutate(Sentiment=line_scores)

Sentiment change over time for specific characters

# function for sentiment score for episodes appeared in sequentially
score_seq <- function(name){
  # filter character data
  char <- got %>%
    filter(Name==name) 
  # arrange by release date
  char$`Release Date` <- ymd(char$`Release Date`)
  char <- char %>%
    arrange(`Release Date`)
  # sequential episodes appeared in
  num_ep <- char %>%
    group_by(`Release Date`) %>%
    arrange(`Release Date`) %>%
    count()
  num_vec <- rep(1:length(unique(num_ep$`Release Date`)), num_ep$n)
  char <- char %>% mutate(conseq_ep=num_vec)
  
  char$Season <- factor(char$Season)
  char
}

Tyrion Lannister sentiment across episodes and seasons

tyrion <- score_seq('tyrion lannister')
ggplot(tyrion, aes(x=conseq_ep, y=Sentiment)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color=Season)) + 
  geom_smooth(color='black') +
  xlab('Sequential episodes appeared in')

Fairly consistent average sentiment scores across seasons for Tyrion, not surprising since he is the most talkative character.

Theon Greyjoy sentiment across episodes and seasons

theon <- score_seq('theon greyjoy')
ggplot(theon, aes(x=conseq_ep, y=Sentiment)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color=Season)) + 
  geom_smooth(color='black') +
  xlab('Sequential episodes appeared in')

The dip in sentiment score in seasons 3 and 4 can be attributed to Theon meeting Ramsay Bolton. Theon manages to escape from Ramsay in season 5 which corresponds to an increasing sentiment score.

# function for getting word cloud for a given character
get_word_cloud <- function(character){
  lines <- got %>% 
    filter(Name==character) %>% 
    select(Sentence)
  
  # collapase all lines to one string
  string <- paste(lines$Sentence, collapse = ' ')[1]
  
  # Create corpus
  corpus = Corpus(VectorSource(string))
  # Conversion to Lowercase
  corpus = tm_map(corpus, PlainTextDocument)
  corpus = tm_map(corpus, tolower)
  # Removing Punctuation
  corpus = tm_map(corpus, removePunctuation)
  # Remove stopwords
  corpus = tm_map(corpus, removeWords, stopwords("english"))
  # Eliminate white spaces
  corpus = tm_map(corpus, stripWhitespace)
  
  DTM <- TermDocumentMatrix(corpus)
  mat <- as.matrix(DTM)
  f <- sort(rowSums(mat),decreasing=TRUE)
  
  # color for words
  rbPal <- colorRampPalette(c('#FF0000', '#FFFFFF', '#0000FF'))
  got_word_scores <- got_word_scores %>% arrange(desc(score))
  got_word_scores$col <- rbPal(20)[as.numeric(cut(got_word_scores$score,breaks = 20))]
  
  # 200 most frequent words and their sentiment scores
  top200 <- tibble(word = names(f),n=f) %>%
    inner_join(got_word_scores, by='word') %>%
    top_n(200, n)
  
  file_name <- paste0(gsub(' ','', character),'.png')
  png(file_name, width=8,height=8, units='in', res=300)
  par(bg='black')
  wordcloud(words = top200$word, freq = top200$n, random.order=F, colors=top200$col, ordered.colors=T) 
  dev.off()
}
get_word_cloud('tyrion lannister')
get_word_cloud('theon greyjoy')
